org.sd.classifier
Class FeatureDictionary

java.lang.Object
  org.sd.classifier.FeatureDictionary

public class FeatureDictionary
extends java.lang.Object

A class to keep track of all feature attributes added to feature vectors for a training set.

A FeatureDictionary that is "unlocked" collects features updated from FeatureVector.setValue (called during feature extraction) while collecting training data.

A "locked" FeatureDictionary is loaded with the features used during training and stored in a trained classifier's ARFF file. When update requests are received on a locked dictionary, the new features are logged for feedback on a classifier's relevance to current input and should be monitored closely for indications that retraining is necessary.

Author:
Spence Koehler, Dave Barney

Constructor Detail

FeatureDictionary

public FeatureDictionary(java.io.File arffFile)
                  throws java.io.IOException
Constructs a Feature Dictionary, which will be loaded from the given ARFF file. The ARFF file must contains a comment that specifies which attribute contains the classification. This comment line must appear BEFORE the @ATTRIBUTE section in the ARFF file. This comment line must also be in the following format: 
 %CLASSIFICATION=attribute_name
or 
 %CLASSIFICATION=attribute_name|constraintsString
The type of the classification attribute is defined by the "@ATTRIBUTE" arff line later in the file as are nominal values. A constraintsString can define the numeric constraints on the attribute if any. If the classification attribute is numeric without constraints, then its values are unbounded.

Parameters:
arffFile - ARFF file to load
Throws:
java.io.IOException

lock

public void lock()
This will lock the Feature Dictionary. There is no way to unlock a Feature Diciontary, so only call once all inteneded inputs are read in.

unlock

public void unlock()
Unlock this dictionary, allowing for feature attribute modifications.

Note that any feature vectors associated with this dictionary may no longer be properly associated with attributes if this dictionary is modified!
